## Local build/preview workflow (merged two-stage site)

A single helper script supports both interactive local preview (serve) and build-only output.

### `serve.py`

`serve.py` builds both MkDocs sites, merges them into one output tree, and either:

- serves them locally (default), or
- builds only (with `--build-only`).

It always mounts the API reference under `/reference/`.

#### Serve mode (default)

Run: `python serve.py`

This builds into a temporary directory and starts a local HTTP server. It prints URLs like:

- `http://127.0.0.1:8000/` (main docs)
- `http://127.0.0.1:8000/reference/` (API reference)

Stop with Ctrl+C. Re-run the script to rebuild.

Useful options:

- `--docs-config mkdocs.yml`
- `--ref-config mkdocs-api-ref.yml`
- `--ref-mount reference`
- `--host 127.0.0.1`
- `--port 0` (auto-pick)
- `--port-start 8000`

#### Build-only mode (`--build-only`)

Run: `python serve.py --build-only --clean`

This builds and merges into a persistent output directory (defaults to `./site`) and does not start a server.

Outputs:

- `site/` (merged main docs)
- `site/reference/` (API reference mounted)

You can override the output directory:

- `python serve.py --build-only --out site --clean`

